sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LexA-Sir2 under a strong constitutive promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Adh1P-LexA(1-87)-Sir2-Adh1t
For targeted (LexA Operators) silencing. Contained in the yeast pRS303 integration vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Horwitz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence for the Sir2 gene with BD ends for Aar1 cloning. Sir2 is a HDAC that we use for silencing in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Quan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since this is a BD part, there is no ATG but it does include a stop codon. For more information on AarI cloning, please refer to the UCSF 2008 igem page.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K106007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a coding sequence for the partial LexA gene with AB ends for Aar1 cloning.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Willis Wong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since this is an AB part, there is a ATG but no stop codon. For more information on AarI cloning, please refer to the UCSF 2008 iGEM page.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: A scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Scar site created by A part ligation. Used for entering composite parts on the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Horwitz
